script(type="text/ng-template", id="about.html")
  .modal-header
    h3.modal-title About
  .modal-body
    p The World Population Project (WPP) aims to make demography - the statistical study of human populations -  accessible to a wider audience. We believe demography and demographic data are key to understanding social and economic phenomena, and that a better appreciation of demographic trends helps individuals see their place in the world.
    h4 Credits
    p The World Population Project has been developed by Wolfgang Fengler, together with KC Samir, Emi Suzuki, Tariq Khokar, <a href="http://benedikt-gross.de/">Benedikt Gro√ü</a> and <a href="http://www.47nord.de/">47 Nord</a>. The project is being supported by the <a href="http://www.worldbank.org/">The World Bank</a> and the International Institute for Applied Systems Analysis (IIASA).
  .modal-footer
    button(ng-click="$close()") Got it!

script(type="text/ng-template", id="developers.html")
  .modal-header
    h3.modal-title Developers
  .modal-body
    p All of the data you see on this World Population Project (WPP) site is comes from a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Representational_state_transfer">restful API</a> which is <a href="http://api.population.io" target="_blank">documented</a> with details of methods and data sources used.
    p The source code behind this site and the API is also available at: <a href="https://github.com/worldpopulation/">github.com/worldpopulation</a> and developers are welcome to build on both the application and API.
  .modal-footer
    button(ng-click="$close()") Got it!

